<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17661022-16">
               <interp inst="t17661022-16" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17661022-16" type="year" value="1766"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17661022-16" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17661022"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17661022-16" type="date" value="17661022"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17661022-16-off82-c163" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-16-defend197 t17661022-16-off82 t17661022-16-verdict85"></join>
         
               <p>491. (M.) 
               <persName id="t17661022-16-defend197" type="defendantName">
                  
                     Elizabeth 
                     Loxham 
                  , otherwise <rs id="t17661022-16-alias-3" type="alias">
                        <join result="nameAlias" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-16-defend197 t17661022-16-alias-3"></join>Jane Gadson</rs>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-defend197" type="surname" value="Loxham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-defend197" type="given" value="Elizabeth"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-defend197" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , <rs id="t17661022-16-deflabel81" type="occupation">spinster</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-16-defend197 t17661022-16-deflabel81"></join>, was indicted for <rs id="t17661022-16-off82" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-off82" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-off82" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one linen sheet, value 4 s. and two bed-curtains, value 4 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17661022-16-victim200" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Brandel 
                  <interp inst="t17661022-16-victim200" type="surname" value="Brandel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-victim200" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-victim200" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-16-off82 t17661022-16-victim200"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17661022-16-cd83" type="crimeDate">Sept, 17</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-16-off82 t17661022-16-cd83"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17661022-16-person201">
                  Mary 
                  Brandel 
               <interp inst="t17661022-16-person201" type="surname" value="Brandel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-person201" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-person201" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am wife to 
               <persName id="t17661022-16-person202">
                  John 
                  Brandel 
               <interp inst="t17661022-16-person202" type="surname" value="Brandel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-person202" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-person202" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , we live in <placeName id="t17661022-16-crimeloc84">Piccadilly</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17661022-16-crimeloc84" type="placeName" value="Piccadilly"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17661022-16-crimeloc84" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-16-off82 t17661022-16-crimeloc84"></join>; the prisoner came to me and desired to have a lodging, and after some difficulty I let her have a room at half a crown a week; I missed a sheet from her bed the very day she went away, which is six weeks ago last Monday.</p>
               <p>Q. How long did she lodge with you?</p>
               <p>M. Brandel. She lodged with me but one week.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you know of her going away?</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176610220015"></xptr>M. Brandel. No, I did not; I missed the bed-curtains out of a trunk in a two pair of stairs room; she had told me she had lived at Justice Girdler's; I went there to know if that was true; there I was told she had robbed them also; the Justice granted me a warrant without any expence. I took her up, and by her confession I found out where the things were sold.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17661022-16-person203">
                  Anne 
                  Joland 
               <interp inst="t17661022-16-person203" type="surname" value="Joland"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-person203" type="given" value="Anne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-person203" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 13th of last month the prisoner brought me two bed curtains to sell.</p>
               <p>Q. What are you?</p>
               <p>A. Joland. I keep a sale-shop in White-lion-street; the prisoner brought the things mentioned to me at two separate times, and I bought them of her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I am an utter stranger in town, and was out of necessaries, or I had not done it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17661022-16-verdict85" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-verdict85" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-verdict85" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
               Guilty of stealing the curtains
            </rs>. <rs id="t17661022-16-punish86" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17661022-16-punish86" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-16-defend197 t17661022-16-punish86"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>There was another indictment against her.</p>
            </div1>
